The Chinese mainland recorded 1,293 new confirmed COVID-19 cases on Monday, with 1,228 linked to local transmissions and 65 from overseas, according to data from the National Health Commission on Tuesday. A total of 5,758 new asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Monday, and 43,425 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. Confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland now total 145,808, with the death toll at 4,638. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 284,683 (43,043 recoveries, 7,420 deaths) Macao: 82 (81 recoveries) Taiwan: 22,896 (13,742 recoveries, 853 deaths)